{"parentUuid":"3201bbff-6c0e-4826-bc35-a22a3882df79","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01ToydZN7hjUf5xdtJXjwy8j","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The three pure-logic batches are converted (I'll build-verify them shortly — wary of the `XCTAssertThrowsError` translations). FluxCore's last file, `MoviesActionsTests`, needs the async `captureDispatches` bridging. I've designed the exact Swift Testing helpers for it; let me delegate the mechanical per-test body conversion to a subagent with those exact helper implementations, running in the background while I convert the app's `@MainActor` suites myself."}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3860,"cache_read_input_tokens":738199,"output_tokens":10222,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3860,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":10222,"cache_read_input_tokens":738199,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3860,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3860},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CbQbs6ET492GxrvCr5RED","attributionMcpServer":"ccd_session","attributionMcpTool":"mark_chapter","type":"assistant","uuid":"bae714b4-7ce3-4540-91f5-f343d0a181c2","timestamp":"2026-05-26T05:09:47.563Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-desktop","cwd":"/Users/scottdensmore/Developer/scottdensmore/movieswiftui","sessionId":"2cae28a4-28e8-4bfa-9225-7682543f3664","version":"2.1.149","gitBranch":"feat/swift-testing-migration","slug":"snuggly-shimmying-pebble"}
{"parentUuid":"bae714b4-7ce3-4540-91f5-f343d0a181c2","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01ToydZN7hjUf5xdtJXjwy8j","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01QHxpmGCWCK6BVFznN5AwVC","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Convert MoviesActionsTests to Swift Testing","subagent_type":"general-purpose","run_in_background":true,"prompt":"Migrate ONE Swift test file from XCTest to Swift Testing. This file is the trickiest in the suite because it bridges completion-handler async work and mutates a shared global. Follow the EXACT helper implementations I give you below — do not improvise the async bridging.\n\nFILE (rewrite in place):\n/Users/scottdensmore/Developer/scottdensmore/movieswiftui/MovieSwift/Packages/MovieSwiftFluxCore/Tests/MovieSwiftFluxCoreTests/MoviesActionsTests.swift\n\nRead it fully first. It currently is `@MainActor final class MoviesActionsTests: XCTestCase` with: nested `StubAPIKeyProvider`, `MockNetworkSession` (NetworkSession, @unchecked Sendable, with a `responseQueue`), `StubError`, a `makeMovie` helper (find it near the bottom), async `setUp()`/`tearDown()` that snapshot & restore `APIService.shared`, a `captureDispatches(waitingFor:until:timeout:when:)` helper using XCTestExpectation, `unwrapDispatched(_:in:file:line:)`, `assertFailureDispatch(...)`, and ~25 `func testX() throws` tests that call `captureDispatches` then assert.\n\n=== STRUCTURAL CHANGES ===\n\n1. `import XCTest` → `import Testing`. Add `import Foundation` (it uses Data, NSLock, DispatchQueue, JSONEncoder). Keep `import Backend`, `import SwiftUIFlux`, `@testable import MovieSwiftFluxCore`.\n\n2. Suite declaration → `@Suite(.serialized) final class MoviesActionsTests {` (REMOVE `@MainActor` and `: XCTestCase`). `.serialized` is REQUIRED because every test mutates the shared global `APIService.shared`, and Swift Testing runs tests in parallel by default.\n\n3. Keep the nested `StubAPIKeyProvider`, `MockNetworkSession`, `StubError`, and `makeMovie` EXACTLY as they are.\n\n4. Replace the async `setUp()`/`tearDown()` overrides with init/deinit:\n```swift\n    private let originalAPIService: APIService\n\n    init() {\n        originalAPIService = APIService.shared\n    }\n\n    deinit {\n        APIService.shared = originalAPIService\n    }\n```\n(Keep the `private var originalAPIService` declaration replaced by the `let` above. Remove the old `override func setUp() async throws { ... }` and `override func tearDown() async throws { ... }`.)\n\n5. Replace the ENTIRE `captureDispatches(...)` helper with this async version (copy verbatim, keep a short doc comment):\n```swift\n    /// Runs an AsyncAction against the synchronous mock session and collects\n    /// every action it dispatches, returning once `trigger` matches one of\n    /// them (or after a 2s safety timeout). Bridges the completion-handler\n    /// dispatch flow to async/await; a lock guards the cross-thread mutation\n    /// and a class box carries the non-Sendable `[Action]` across the\n    /// continuation.\n    private func captureDispatches(\n        until trigger: @escaping (Action) -> Bool,\n        when execute: (@escaping DispatchFunction) -> Void\n    ) async -> [Action] {\n        final class Collector: @unchecked Sendable {\n            let lock = NSLock()\n            var dispatched: [Action] = []\n            var didResume = false\n        }\n        struct Box: @unchecked Sendable { let actions: [Action] }\n        let collector = Collector()\n        return await withCheckedContinuation { (continuation: CheckedContinuation<Box, Never>) in\n            execute { action in\n                collector.lock.lock()\n                collector.dispatched.append(action)\n                let shouldResume = trigger(action) && !collector.didResume\n                if shouldResume { collector.didResume = true }\n                let snapshot = collector.dispatched\n                collector.lock.unlock()\n                if shouldResume { continuation.resume(returning: Box(actions: snapshot)) }\n            }\n            DispatchQueue.global().asyncAfter(deadline: .now() + 2.0) {\n                collector.lock.lock()\n                let shouldResume = !collector.didResume\n                if shouldResume { collector.didResume = true }\n                let snapshot = collector.dispatched\n                collector.lock.unlock()\n                if shouldResume { continuation.resume(returning: Box(actions: snapshot)) }\n            }\n        }.actions\n    }\n```\n\n6. Replace `unwrapDispatched` and `assertFailureDispatch` with these (note `sourceLocation: SourceLocation = #_sourceLocation` replaces the old `file:`/`line:` params, so failures still point at the call site):\n```swift\n    private func unwrapDispatched<T>(\n        _ type: T.Type,\n        in dispatched: [Action],\n        sourceLocation: SourceLocation = #_sourceLocation\n    ) throws -> T {\n        let matches = dispatched.compactMap { $0 as? T }\n        return try #require(matches.first,\n                            \"Expected one \\(T.self) in dispatched actions, got: \\(dispatched)\",\n                            sourceLocation: sourceLocation)\n    }\n\n    private func assertFailureDispatch(\n        in dispatched: [Action],\n        for key: LoadingKey,\n        noDataActionMatching matches: (Action) -> Bool,\n        dataActionDescription: String,\n        sourceLocation: SourceLocation = #_sourceLocation\n    ) throws -> MoviesListLoadFailure {\n        let unwantedDataAction = dispatched.first(where: matches)\n        #expect(unwantedDataAction == nil,\n                \"Failure path unexpectedly dispatched a \\(dataActionDescription) data action.\",\n                sourceLocation: sourceLocation)\n        let loadingStates = dispatched.compactMap { $0 as? MoviesActions.SetLoadingState }\n        let lastForKey = loadingStates.last { $0.key == key }\n        let unwrapped = try #require(lastForKey,\n                                     \"No SetLoadingState dispatched for key \\(key); got: \\(loadingStates)\",\n                                     sourceLocation: sourceLocation)\n        guard case let .failed(failure) = unwrapped.state else {\n            Issue.record(\"Last SetLoadingState for \\(key) was \\(String(describing: unwrapped.state)), not .failed\",\n                         sourceLocation: sourceLocation)\n            throw StubError.failed\n        }\n        return failure\n    }\n```\nKeep the existing explanatory doc comments above these helpers.\n\n=== PER-TEST CHANGES ===\n\n7. Every `func testFoo() throws { ... }` → `@Test func foo() async throws { ... }` (drop leading `test`, ALWAYS add `async` because `captureDispatches` is now async).\n\n8. Update every call site of the old helper. The old form was:\n   `let dispatched = captureDispatches(waitingFor: \"some desc\", until: { ... }, when: { dispatch in ... })`\n   (some calls also pass `timeout:`). The NEW form drops `waitingFor:` and `timeout:` and adds `await`:\n   `let dispatched = await captureDispatches(until: { ... }, when: { dispatch in ... })`\n   Calls to `try unwrapDispatched(X.self, in: dispatched)` and `try assertFailureDispatch(in: dispatched, for: ..., noDataActionMatching: ..., dataActionDescription: ...)` stay the same MINUS any `file:`/`line:` arguments (remove those — the default sourceLocation handles it).\n\n9. Assertion mapping for the remaining direct asserts in test bodies:\n   - `XCTAssertEqual(a, b)` → `#expect(a == b)` (msg → 2nd arg). Split on TOP-LEVEL comma respecting nested brackets/strings.\n   - `XCTAssertNil(x)` → `#expect(x == nil)`; `XCTAssertNotNil(x)` → `#expect(x != nil)`\n   - `XCTAssertTrue(x)` → `#expect(x)`; `XCTAssertFalse(x)` → `#expect(!(x))`\n   - `XCTAssertGreaterThan`→`>`, `…GreaterThanOrEqual`→`>=`, `…LessThan`→`<`, `…LessThanOrEqual`→`<=`\n   - `try XCTUnwrap(x)` → `try #require(x)`\n   - `XCTFail(\"msg\")` → `Issue.record(\"msg\")`\n   - Parenthesize `??` (and other low-precedence) LHS before `==`.\n\n10. Keep ALL `// MARK:` lines, comments, and the test order. Keep `APIService.shared = APIService(...)` setup lines inside tests AS-IS.\n\nAfter rewriting: confirm zero `XCTAssert*`/`XCTUnwrap`/`XCTFail`/`XCTestCase`/`waitForExpectations`/`expectation(`/`import XCTest` remain; the suite is `@Suite(.serialized) final class`; every test is `@Test func ... async throws`. Do NOT build (sibling files still mid-migration). Report: number of `@Test` methods and confirmation of the above."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3860,"cache_read_input_tokens":738199,"output_tokens":10222,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3860,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":10222,"cache_read_input_tokens":738199,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3860,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3860},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CbQbs6ET492GxrvCr5RED","attributionMcpServer":"ccd_session","attributionMcpTool":"mark_chapter","type":"assistant","uuid":"32685df5-171e-4f53-ab35-7097a44cd375","timestamp":"2026-05-26T05:10:20.118Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-desktop","cwd":"/Users/scottdensmore/Developer/scottdensmore/movieswiftui","sessionId":"2cae28a4-28e8-4bfa-9225-7682543f3664","version":"2.1.149","gitBranch":"feat/swift-testing-migration","slug":"snuggly-shimmying-pebble"}
