ngFor:` and `timeout:` and adds `await`:\n   `let dispatched = await captureDispatches(until: { ... }, when: { dispatch in ... })`\n   Calls to `try unwrapDispatched(X.self, in: dispatched)` and `try assertFailureDispatch(in: dispatched, for: ..., noDataActionMatching: ..., dataActionDescription: ...)` stay the same MINUS any `file:`/`line:` arguments (remove those — the default sourceLocation handles it).\n\n9. Assertion mapping for the remaining direct asserts in test bodies:\n   - `XCTAssertEqual(a, b)` → `#expect(a == b)` (msg → 2nd arg). Split on TOP-LEVEL comma respecting nested brackets/strings.\n   - `XCTAssertNil(x)` → `#expect(x == nil)`; `XCTAssertNotNil(x)` → `#expect(x != nil)`\n   - `XCTAssertTrue(x)` → `#expect(x)`; `XCTAssertFalse(x)` → `#expect(!(x))`\n   - `XCTAssertGreaterThan`→`>`, `…GreaterThanOrEqual`→`>=`, `…LessThan`→`<`, `…LessThanOrEqual`→`<=`\n   - `try XCTUnwrap(x)` → `try #require(x)`\n   - `XCTFail(\"msg\")` → `Issue.record(\"msg\")`\n   - Parenthesize `??` (and other low-precedence) LHS before `==`.\n\n10. Keep ALL `// MARK:` lines, comments, and the test order. Keep `APIService.shared = APIService(...)` setup lines inside tests AS-IS.\n\nAfter rewriting: confirm zero `XCTAssert*`/`XCTUnwrap`/`XCTFail`/`XCTestCase`/`waitForExpectations`/`expectation(`/`import XCTest` remain; the suite is `@Suite(.serialized) final class`; every test is `@Test func ... async throws`. Do NOT build (sibling files still mid-migration). Report: number of `@Test` methods and confirmation of the above.","outputFile":"/private/tmp/claude-501/-Users-scottdensmore-Developer-scottdensmore-movieswiftui/73bfc67d-407a-421c-bdf6-b48fa3a353d2/tasks/a7b9c819e1101077f.output","canReadOutputFile":true},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"32685df5-171e-4f53-ab35-7097a44cd375","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-desktop","cwd":"/Users/scottdensmore/Developer/scottdensmore/movieswiftui","sessionId":"2cae28a4-28e8-4bfa-9225-7682543f3664","version":"2.1.149","gitBranch":"feat/s