e app's own XCTest-environment detection and are not framework references.)\n\n**Key conversions applied:**\n- `import XCTest` → `import Testing`; added `import Foundation`; kept `import MovieSwiftFluxCore` and the `#if os(macOS) @testable import Film_O_Matic #else @testable import MovieSwift #endif` block exactly.\n- Class → `@Suite @MainActor struct MovieSwiftTests {` with the `// @MainActor:` comment preserved. No `.serialized`/`async` added.\n- Each `func testFoo()` → `@Test func foo()`, preserving `throws` where present and all `#if !os(macOS)` guards and the `// MARK:` header.\n- All assertion forms converted per the rules (`==`, `!=`, `== nil`, `!= nil`, `#expect(x)`, `#expect(!(x))`, comparison operators). Multiline assertions with arrays/Sets/dictionaries containing internal commas were split on the top-level comma only. Helper methods `makeMovie`/`makePerson` left untouched. No LHS required `??` parenthesization.\n\nPer your project guidance I did not build (siblings are mid-migration).</result>\n<usage><total_tokens>146404</total_tokens><tool_uses>86</tool_uses><duration_ms>650399</duration_ms></usage>\n</task-notification>"}
