{"parentUuid":"8d7c24a5-b71f-4af3-9a40-459567d35e33","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"8aefd606-8e8e-4eb8-b0fd-c305e26dd4b8","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BBM4twXHYKcKp4JWXNbMpu","type":"tool_result","content":"=== inline comments ===\n[APIServiceTests.swift#118] Using `try? #require(...)` here discards the failure context if `lastRequest`/`url` is nil, and forces the rest of the assertions to operate on optionals. Prefer making this test `async throws` and using `let requestURL = try #require(sessi\n[AppDataICloudBackupTests.swift#29] Suite-level `init() throws` means any temp-directory creation failure will surface as a suite construction failure rather than a specific `@Test` failure, which can make diagnosis harder. Consider making the initializer non-throwing and per\n=== reviews ===\ncopilot-pull-request-reviewer[bot]: COMMENTED\n=== mergeable ===\nmergeable=MERGEABLE state=BLOCKED","is_error":false}]},"uuid":"c090839b-e16f-43d2-a4f0-24a95031573d","timestamp":"2026-05-27T02:24:51.748Z","toolUseResult":{"stdout":"=== inline comments ===\n[APIServiceTests.swift#118] Using `try? #require(...)` here discards the failure context if `lastRequest`/`url` is nil, and forces the rest of the assertions to operate on optionals. Prefer making this test `async throws` and using `let requestURL = try #require(sessi\n[AppDataICloudBackupTests.swift#29] Suite-level `init() throws` means any temp-directory creation failure will surface as a suite construction failure rather than a specific `@Test` failure, which can make diagnosis harder. Consider making the initializer non-throwing and per\n=== reviews ===\ncopilot-pull-request-reviewer[bot]: COMMENTED\n=== mergeable ===\nmergeable=MERGEABLE state=BLOCKED","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"8d7c24a5-b71f-4af3-9a40-459567d35e33","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-desktop","cwd":"/Users/scottdensmore/Developer/scot