{"parentUuid":"d9880f90-380c-4f08-8456-9e230831f604","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01QEm3u8fr8of2SQLedNT8FZ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_016jCWnMpbjerLNXNgmX4Ypi","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"git fetch origin main --quiet && echo \"behind: $(git rev-list --count HEAD..origin/main)\" && git push -u origin feat/deprecation-cleanup 2>&1 | tail -2 && gh pr create --repo scottdensmore/MovieSwiftUI --base main --head feat/deprecation-cleanup --title \"refactor(ui): replace deprecated .cornerRadius; drop dead @available gates\" --body \"$(cat <<'EOF'\n## Summary\nPost-modernization audit cleanups (no behavior change):\n- **`.cornerRadius(_:)` → `.clipShape(RoundedRectangle(cornerRadius:))`** — 14 sites across the app and UI package. `.cornerRadius` is soft-deprecated in iOS 17; the clip-shape form is the modern equivalent and renders identically (circular corners).\n- **Removed two always-true `@available` version gates** now that the deployment minimum is 26: `@available(iOS 14.0, macOS 12.0, *)` on `MetricKitCrashReporter.didReceive(_:[MXDiagnosticPayload])` and `@available(iOS 13.0, OSX 10.15, *)` on `SearchField`. The `@available(tvOS, unavailable)` / `watchOS, unavailable` gates on `SearchField` are kept (intentional platform exclusions).\n\n## Test plan\nRender-identical modifier swap + dead-code removal — the compiler is the verification.\n- [x] iOS (`MovieSwift`), macOS (`MovieSwiftMac`), tvOS (`MovieSwiftTV`) — BUILD SUCCEEDED, 0 warnings.\n- [ ] CI: full matrix.\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\nEOF\n)\" 2>&1 | tail -2","description":"Push and create PR A"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1331,"cache_read_input_tokens":879044,"output_tokens":732,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tie