{"parentUuid":"b5d93747-691a-4a69-a903-698a731fd35d","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01XBqPTdaGc2faFhwoVTDr12","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01RXuF9Gq6wuxkoVZGTiVfiM","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"git commit -m \"$(cat <<'EOF'\nrefactor(images): modernize image loading from Combine to async/await + @Observable\n\n- ImageService.fetchImage: replace the Combine `dataTaskPublisher` /\n  AnyPublisher with an `async` method over `URLSession.data(from:)`,\n  returning nil on transport error (same contract as the old\n  `.catch { Just(nil) }`). Drop the Combine/SwiftUI imports.\n- ImageLoader: convert from `ObservableObject` + `@Published` + a Combine\n  `AnyCancellable` to a `@MainActor @Observable` class that loads via an\n  unstructured `Task` (download off-main, publish `image` on the main\n  actor); the task is cancelled in deinit. ImageLoaderCache is now\n  `@MainActor` (its loaders are created/read on the main actor).\n- ImageService.Size conforms to Sendable (trivial raw-value enum) so it\n  can cross into the loading Task.\n- Consumers: the ~12 image views switch `@ObservedObject var imageLoader`\n  to a plain `var` (an @Observable object is observed by reading it in\n  `body`), and CarouselImageView's `@StateObject` becomes `@State`.\n\nBehavior-preserving; Backend builds with 0 warnings and its 40 tests\npass; iOS/macOS/tvOS app targets build clean.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>\nEOF\n)\" 2>&1 | tail -2 && git fetch origin main --quiet && echo \"behind: $(git rev-list --count HEAD..origin/main)\"","description":"Commit async image loading and check branch sync"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1006,"cache_read_input_tokens":918772,"output_tokens":644,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1006,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":644,"cache_read_input_tokens":918772,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1006,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1006},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CbSSWpLdgc3nCvWog29s6","type":"assistant","uuid":"c79a4f3d-893f-47f5-a13d-2adf66b402ba","timestamp":"2026-05-27T04:27:11.495Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-desktop","cwd":"/Users/scottdensmore/Developer/scottdensmore/movieswiftui","sessionId":"2cae28a4-28e8-4bfa-9225-7682543f3664","version":"2.1.149","gitBranch":"feat/async-image-loading","slug":"snuggly-shimmying-pebble"}
{"parentUuid":"c79a4f3d-893f-47f5-a13d-2adf66b402ba","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"78d19742-02b9-4f99-acaa-4a7e2e2c4776","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RXuF9Gq6wuxkoVZGTiVfiM","type":"tool_result","content":"[feat/async-image-loading 8f6fe89] refactor(images): modernize image loading from Combine to async/await + @Observable\n 12 files changed, 52 insertions(+), 47 deletions(-)\nbehind: 0","is_error":false}]},"uuid":"2dde0774-3fa0-4f8b-b512-3e9ded748b76","timestamp":"2026-05-27T04:27:41.390Z","toolUseResult":{"stdout":"[feat/async-image-loading 8f6fe89] refactor(images): modernize image loading from Combine to async/await + @Observable\n 12 files changed, 52 insertions(+), 47 deletions(-)\nbehind: 0","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"c79a4f3d-893f-47f5-a13d-2adf66b402ba","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-desktop","cwd":"/Users/scottdensmore/Developer/scottdensmore/movieswiftui","sessionId":"2cae28a4-28e8-4bfa-9225-7682543f3664","version":"2.1.149","gitBranch":"feat/async-image-loading","slug":"snuggly-shimmying-pebble"}
{"parentUuid":"2dde0774-3fa0-4f8b-b512-3e9ded748b76","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01H6MoGYUGv6kvacFHWvKAWs","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01EmUdmQmoqjBd6Pf2XptVwC","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"git push -u origin feat/async-image-loading 2>&1 | tail -2 && gh pr create --repo scottdensmore/MovieSwiftUI --base main --head feat/async-image-loading --title \"refactor(images): Combine → async/await + @Observable image loading\" --body \"$(cat <<'EOF'\n## Summary\nModernizes the last Combine-based corner of the app — image loading — to structured concurrency + the Observation framework.\n\n- **`ImageService.fetchImage`**: `AnyPublisher<Data?, Never>` (Combine `dataTaskPublisher`) → `async -> Data?` over `URLSession.data(from:)`, returning `nil` on transport error (same contract as the old `.catch { Just(nil) }`). Combine/SwiftUI imports dropped.\n- **`ImageLoader`**: `ObservableObject` + `@Published image` + a Combine `AnyCancellable` → a `@MainActor @Observable` class that loads via an unstructured `Task` (download off-main, publish `image` on the main actor; task cancelled in `deinit`). `ImageLoaderCache` is now `@MainActor`.\n- **`ImageService.Size`** conforms to `Sendable` (trivial raw-value enum) so it can cross into the loading `Task`.\n- **Consumers** (~12 image views): `@ObservedObject var imageLoader` → plain `var` (an `@Observable` object is observed by reading it in `body`); `CarouselImageView`'s `@StateObject` → `@State`.\n\nThis removes the remaining `ObservableObject`/`@Published`/`AnyPublisher` usage outside the pinned SwiftUIFlux `Store`.\n\n## Test plan\nBehavior-preserving refactor (image loading semantics unchanged; the network path wasn't unit-tested before or after).\n- [x] `swift test` — Backend: 40 tests pass (including the cache-identity `ImageLoaderCacheTests`); 0 warnings.\n- [x] iOS / macOS / tvOS app targets build clean, 0 warnings.\n- [ ] CI: full matrix.\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\nEOF\n)\" 2>&1 | tail -2","description":"Push and create PR B"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":724,"cache_read_input_tokens":919778,"output_tokens":863,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":724,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":863,"cache_read_input_tokens":919778,"cache_creation_input_tokens":724,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":724},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CbSSZoTPMrzDeqjMqe5Dw","type":"assistant","uuid":"ca49899b-e5bf-4aa1-a564-759912851b80","timestamp":"2026-05-27T04:27:52.555Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-desktop","cwd":"/Users/scottdensmore/Developer/scottdensmore/movieswiftui","sessionId":"2cae28a4-28e8-4bfa-9225-7682543f3664","version":"2.1.149","gitBranch":"feat/async-image-loading","slug":"snuggly-shimmying-pebble"}
