{"parentUuid":"d383dba1-ff19-4e02-9351-608875bae846","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_018ZC55Nfk998NqjotaQ1Qas","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Done. Both audit-driven cleanups merged.\n\n## Audit refresh — both PRs merged\n\n| PR | Audit fix | What landed |\n|----|-----------|-------------|\n| #13 | A | 14 sites of `.cornerRadius(_:)` → `.clipShape(RoundedRectangle(cornerRadius:))`; removed two always-true `@available` version gates (MetricKit iOS14/macOS12, SearchField iOS13/macOS10.15) |\n| #14 | B | `ImageService.fetchImage`: Combine `AnyPublisher`/`dataTaskPublisher` → `async -> Data?`; `ImageLoader`: `ObservableObject`+`@Published`+`AnyCancellable` → `@MainActor @Observable` + `Task`; `ImageLoaderCache` → `@MainActor`; ~12 consumer views switched from `@ObservedObject`/`@StateObject` to plain `var`/`@State` |\n\nBoth Copilot comments addressed cleanly (a wording nit on the `@available` comment in #13; a fair scope-correction on #14's description — I'd overstated, since `SearchTextObservable`'s Combine debounce stays). All threads resolved, full CI matrix green on both merges.\n\n## What's left (intentionally)\n\n- **`SearchTextObservable`** (UI package) — still on `ObservableObject` + `@Published` + a Combine `debounce` pipeline. Kept on Combine because the debounce is a natural Combine fit and the class is `open` and subclassed by app view models (`MoviesSearchTextWrapper` et al.); converting would cascade through those subclasses and reimplement debounce with `Task.sleep`-style code without clear benefit.\n- **SwiftUIFlux `Store`** (`ObservableObject` / `@EnvironmentObject` / `@StateObject` / `@ObservedObject` usages) — bound to the pinned external dependency; can't migrate without forking it.\n\nSo the modernization tree is now clean down to those two well-understood holdouts. The audited 6 items are done, the post-audit cleanups (A and B) are done — total **8 PRs merged** in this session (#7, #8, #9, #10, #11, #12, #13, #14). If you spot anything else worth tackling later, just let me know."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":111,"cache_read_input_tokens":948938,"output_tokens":774,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":111,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":774,"cache_read_input_tokens":948938,"cache_creation_input_tokens":111,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":111},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CbXw6BihygTpq3oTFGjL5","type":"assistant","uuid":"4d98668f-4450-4b28-a061-af76238425ab","timestamp":"2026-05-30T02:05:07.029Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-desktop","cwd":"/Users/scottdensmore/Developer/scottdensmore/movieswiftui","sessionId":"2cae28a4-28e8-4bfa-9225-7682543f3664","version":"2.1.149","gitBranch":"main","slug":"snuggly-shimmying-pebble"}
