{"parentUuid":null,"logicalParentUuid":"836cd6c1-d81c-4d3f-9d1c-44cd3e3af932","isSidechain":false,"type":"system","subtype":"compact_boundary","content":"Conversation compacted","isMeta":false,"timestamp":"2026-05-30T02:20:55.110Z","uuid":"f9f2708a-1969-4214-b235-47692fad0925","level":"info","compactMetadata":{"trigger":"auto","preTokens":969875,"preCompactDiscoveredTools":["CronCreate","ExitPlanMode","Monitor","PushNotification","RemoteTrigger","TaskCreate","TaskList","TaskOutput","TaskStop","TaskUpdate","TodoWrite","mcp__ccd_session_mgmt__search_session_transcripts","mcp__xcode__BuildProject","mcp__xcode__GetBuildLog"],"postTokens":6883,"durationMs":147622},"userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-desktop","cwd":"/Users/scottdensmore/Developer/scottdensmore/movieswiftui","sessionId":"2cae28a4-28e8-4bfa-9225-7682543f3664","version":"2.1.149","gitBranch":"main","slug":"snuggly-shimmying-pebble"}
{"parentUuid":"f9f2708a-1969-4214-b235-47692fad0925","isSidechain":false,"promptId":"af759ad8-76cc-4b58-b2d3-322690ab2306","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.\n\nSummary:\n1. Primary Request and Intent:\n   The user is modernizing the MovieSwiftUI app (SwiftUI iOS/macOS/tvOS). In this session, the user requested:\n   (a) Begin Modernization 6 of the audited list — finish XCTest → Swift Testing migration.\n   (b) \"Yes lets do a quick refresh to see if you find anything else\" — do another audit pass to find remaining modernization opportunities; the user then selected all three findings (cornerRadius sweep, dead @available cleanup, Combine→async image loading).\n   (c) \"Yes lets do a quick refresh to see if you find anything else\" (a second time) — another audit pass.\n   (d) Most recent: \"Are the tests modern syntax?\" — asking whether the test code itself uses modern test patterns beyond just the framework migration.\n   \n   User-stated workflow constraints (continuing from earlier session): create feature branch → PR → all required CI green → address Copilot comments → resolve threads → merge → delete branch → return to main. Always use `gh` CLI for GitHub operations. Always write tests for fixes (CLAUDE.md). No Xcode template file headers in new files. Don't commit secrets/.claude/.entire local settings. Per-PR workflow per modernization item.\n\n2. Key Technical Concepts:\n   - Swift Testing framework: `@Suite`, `@Test`, `#expect`, `#require`, `Issue.record`, `.serialized`, `@MainActor` on suites, `SourceLocation = #_sourceLocation`.\n   - Concurrency-aware suite kinds: `@Suite struct` (parallel-safe pure), `@Suite @MainActor struct` (main-actor app code), `@Suite(.serialized) final class` (shared global/file state, init/deinit lifecycle).\n   - Async-bridging patterns: `withCheckedContinuation` + `@unchecked Sendable` boxes (ResultBox, ActionsBox) to carry non-Sendable Result/[Action] across the continuation.\n   - Helper signature for source attribution: `sourceLocation: SourceLocation = #_sourceLocation` passed to `#expect`/`#require`/`Issue.record`.\n   - Swift Testing macro pitfalls: `#require` can't be nested; key-path predicates inside `#require` confuse throws inference; `#expect { } throws: { }` closure-matcher form is deprecated (use do/catch + Issue.record); `return Issue.record(...)` fails (Issue.record returns Issue, not Void).\n   - XCUITest constraint: Swift Testing cannot drive XCUIApplication; XCUITest files must remain XCTest.\n   - Swift 6 strict concurrency: Sendable on raw-value enums, @MainActor classes implicitly Sendable, @Observation + @MainActor with `@ObservationIgnored` for non-observed properties, Task inherits actor isolation from creation context.\n   - SwiftUI Observation: `@Observable` macro vs ObservableObject; consumers use plain `var` (auto-tracked in body) for passed-in @Observable; `@State` for owned @Observable; `State(wrappedValue:)` constructor.\n   - Deprecation modernizations: `.cornerRadius(_:)` → `.clipShape(RoundedRectangle(cornerRadius:))`; dead `@available` gates removable when deployment minimum surpasses them; Combine `AnyPublisher`/`dataTaskPublisher` → async/await `URLSession.data(from:)`.\n   - GitHub workflow: branch protection `strict=true` (branch up-to-date with main), `required_conversation_resolution=enabled` (all Copilot threads resolved before merge); GraphQL `addPullRequestReviewThreadReply` + `resolveReviewThread`; merge with `gh pr merge --merge --delete-branch`.\n\n3. Files and Code Sections:\n   \n   **Modernization 6 — PR #12 (merged, b978a3c, 5af16f0, da94bcb)**:\n   \n   - `MovieSwift/Packages/Backend/Tests/BackendTests/APIKeyProviderTests.swift`\n     - Converted to `@Suite(.serialized) final class APIKeyProviderTests` with `init()`/`deinit` snapshotting `AppUserDefaults.userTMDBAPIKey`.\n     - Gold-standard for serialized-class pattern.\n   \n   - `MovieSwift/Packages/Backend/Tests/BackendTests/APIServiceTests.swift`\n     - `@Suite struct APIServiceTests` with private `ResultBox<T>: @unchecked Sendable { let result: Result<T, APIService.APIError> }`.\n     - Async `get<T: Codable & Sendable>(...)` helper bridging completion handler:\n       ```swift\n       await withCheckedContinuation { continuation in\n           service.GET(endpoint:, params:) { (result: Result<T, APIService.APIError>) in\n               continuation.resume(returning: ResultBox(result: result))\n           }\n       }.result\n       ```\n     - Per Copilot review: `getBuildsRequestAndDecodesOnSuccess` made `async throws` with `try #require(session.lastRequest?.url)` instead of `try?`.\n   \n   - `MovieSwift/Packages/MovieSwiftFluxCore/Tests/MovieSwiftFluxCoreTests/MoviesActionsTests.swift`\n     - `@Suite(.serialized) final class` with init/deinit for APIService.shared snapshot/restore.\n     - Async `captureDispatches(until:when:)` helper with internal `Collector: @unchecked Sendable` class (NSLock + dispatched + didResume) + `Box: @unchecked Sendable { let actions: [Action] }` + 2s safety timeout via `DispatchQueue.global().asyncAfter`.\n     - Helpers `unwrapDispatched<T>` and `assertFailureDispatch` take `sourceLocation: SourceLocation = #_sourceLocation`.\n     - Fixed nested `#require`: `try #require(URLComponents(url: try #require(session.lastRequest?.url), ...))` split into two statements.\n   \n   - `MovieSwift/MovieSwiftTests/PeopleActionsTests.swift`\n     - `@Suite(.serialized) final class` with `import SwiftUIFlux` (for Action/DispatchFunction types in helpers — initially missed).\n     - Two collect helpers: `collectDispatches(until:when:)` (until-match or 2s timeout) and `collectDispatches(forSeconds:when:)` (fixed window for inverted \"does not dispatch\" cases).\n   \n   - `MovieSwift/MovieSwiftTests/ErrorDiagnosticTests.swift`\n     - `@Suite @MainActor struct`. `XCTSkipUnless` → early `return` (no mid-test skip in Swift Testing).\n   \n   - `MovieSwift/MovieSwiftTests/AppDataICloudBackupTests.swift`\n     - `@Suite(.serialized) final class` with `init()` (non-throwing per Copilot, using `try?` on tempContainer creation).\n     - 2 `#expect { } throws: { error in ... return Bool }` blocks fixed → `do/catch + Issue.record` pattern.\n     - Fixed `try #require(versions.first(where: \\.isCurrent), ...)` → `try #require(versions.first(where: { $0.isCurrent }), ...)` (key path confused throws inference).\n   \n   - `MovieSwift/MovieSwiftTests/CrashReportStoreTests.swift`\n     - Similar `#expect { } throws: { }` fixed to do/catch.\n   \n   - `MovieSwift/MovieSwiftTests/MovieSwiftTests.swift` (2277 lines, 197 tests)\n     - `@Suite @MainActor struct`, 410 #expect calls, 1 Issue.record.\n     - Fixed `return Issue.record(\"...\")` in Void function → `Issue.record(\"...\"); return`.\n   \n   **Audit fix A — PR #13 (merged, 1cf45cc)**:\n   \n   - Sed: 14 occurrences of `.cornerRadius(\\([0-9]*\\))` → `.clipShape(RoundedRectangle(cornerRadius: \\1))` across 10 files (PeopleImage, DiscoverCoverImage, DiscoverView, CustomListRow, BottomMenu, MovieButtonsRow, PosterStyle, BorderedButton, RoundedBadge, NotificationBadge).\n   \n   - `MovieSwift/Shared/flux/state/MetricKitCrashReporter.swift`: removed `@available(iOS 14.0, macOS 12.0, *)` from `didReceive(_ payloads: [MXDiagnosticPayload])`.\n   \n   - `MovieSwift/Packages/UI/Sources/UI/fields/SearchField.swift`: removed `@available(iOS 13.0, OSX 10.15, *)`, kept `@available(tvOS, unavailable)` / `watchOS, unavailable`. Per Copilot nit: comment wording \"OSX 10.15\" → \"macOS 10.15\".\n   \n   **Audit fix B — PR #14 (merged, 8f6fe89)**:\n   \n   - `MovieSwift/Packages/Backend/Sources/Backend/services/ImageService.swift`:\n     ```swift\n     public final class ImageService: Sendable {\n         public static let shared = ImageService()\n         public enum Size: String, Sendable { case small = \"...\", medium = \"...\", cast = \"...\", original = \"...\" }\n         public func fetchImage(poster: String, size: Size) async -> Data? {\n             do {\n                 let (data, _) = try await URLSession.shared.data(from: size.path(poster: poster))\n                 return data\n             } catch { return nil }\n         }\n     }\n     ```\n     - Dropped `import SwiftUI`, `import Combine`.\n     - Added `Sendable` to `Size` enum (fixed \"sending 'size' risks causing data races\" in Task capture).\n   \n   - `MovieSwift/Packages/Backend/Sources/Backend/utils/ImageLoader.swift`:\n     ```swift\n     import Foundation\n     import Observation\n     \n     @MainActor\n     public final class ImageLoaderCache {\n         public static let shared = ImageLoaderCache()\n         private let loaders: NSCache<NSString, ImageLoader> = NSCache()\n         public func loaderFor(path: String?, size: ImageService.Size) -> ImageLoader { ... }\n         public func clear() { loaders.removeAllObjects() }\n     }\n     \n     @MainActor\n     @Observable\n     public final class ImageLoader {\n         public let path: String?\n         public let size: ImageService.Size\n         public var image: Data?\n         @ObservationIgnored private var loadTask: Task<Void, Never>?\n         public init(path: String?, size: ImageService.Size) { ...; loadImage() }\n         private func loadImage() {\n             guard let poster = path, image == nil else { return }\n             loadTask = Task { [weak self, size] in\n                 let data = await ImageService.shared.fetchImage(poster: poster, size: size)\n                 self?.image = data\n             }\n         }\n         deinit { loadTask?.cancel() }\n     }\n     ```\n   \n   - `MovieSwift/Packages/Backend/Tests/BackendTests/ImageLoaderCacheTests.swift`: added `@MainActor` to suite.\n   \n   - `MovieSwift/MovieSwift/views/shared/images/ImagesCarouselView.swift`: `@StateObject private var loader: ImageLoader` → `@State private var loader: ImageLoader`; `self._loader = StateObject(wrappedValue: ...)` → `self._loader = State(wrappedValue: ...)`.\n   \n   - ~12 consumer view files: `@ObservedObject var imageLoader: ImageLoader` → `var imageLoader: ImageLoader` (BigMoviePosterImage, PeopleImage (x2), MovieBackdropImage, MovieTopBackdropImage, FullscreenMoviePosterImage, DiscoverCoverImage, CustomListRow, MoviePosterImage shared).\n\n4. Errors and fixes:\n   \n   - **Nested `#require` macro recursion** in MoviesActionsTests (subagent output): `try #require(URLComponents(url: try #require(...)))` → split into 2 statements: `let requestURL = try #require(...)` then `let components = try #require(URLComponents(url: requestURL, ...))`. Fixed at MoviesActionsTests lines 204-206 and 369-371.\n   \n   - **Deprecated `#expect { } throws: { }` closure-matcher** form (subagent output in CrashReportStoreTests + AppDataICloudBackupTests): converted 3 sites to `do { try expr; Issue.record(\"Expected throw\") } catch { guard case ... = error else { Issue.record(...); return } }`.\n   \n   - **Missing `import SwiftUIFlux`** in my PeopleActionsTests rewrite — `Action` and `DispatchFunction` are SwiftUIFlux types used in collectDispatches helpers. Added the import.\n   \n   - **Key-path predicate confuses `#require` throws inference**: `try #require(versions.first(where: \\.isCurrent), ...)` → `try #require(versions.first(where: { $0.isCurrent }), ...)`. Error was \"call can throw, but it is not marked with 'try'\" in macro expansion.\n   \n   - **`return Issue.record(...)` in Void function** in MovieSwiftTests (subagent output at line 1670): `Issue.record` returns Issue (unlike XCTFail which returns Void). Split into `Issue.record(\"...\"); return`.\n   \n   - **\"sending 'size' risks causing data races\"** in ImageLoader.loadImage Task capture: `ImageService.Size` enum wasn't `Sendable`. Added `Sendable` to `public enum Size: String, Sendable`.\n   \n   - **Copilot review on PR #12**: `APIServiceTests.getBuildsRequestAndDecodesOnSuccess` used `try? #require(...)` which silently degraded subsequent assertions to optionals. Made test `async throws` and used `try #require` (non-optional). Also AppDataICloudBackupTests `init() throws` → non-throwing init with `try?` on temp-dir creation (so failure surfaces in specific @Test, not opaque suite-construction failure).\n   \n   - **Copilot review on PR #13**: Comment said \"OSX 10.15\" — updated wording to \"macOS 10.15\" (modern platform name).\n   \n   - **Copilot review on PR #14**: PR description overstated \"removes the remaining ObservableObject/@Published/Combine usage outside SwiftUIFlux Store\" — `SearchTextObservable` (UI package) still uses Combine debounce. Corrected PR body with scope note that this is image-loading only; SearchTextObservable's Combine debounce intentionally stays (debounce is natural Combine fit, type is `open` and subclassed by app view models).\n\n5. Problem Solving:\n   \n   - Modernization 6 completed and merged via PR #12 (8 commits: backend conversion, fluxcore conversion, app conversion, review fix).\n   - First audit refresh identified 3 actionable items; all three completed and merged as PR #13 (cornerRadius + dead @available) and PR #14 (Combine→async image loading).\n   - Second audit refresh confirmed codebase is clean — all flagged patterns turned out to be false positives (`.navigationBarTitle...` matches were all `.navigationBarTitleDisplayMode`; `.onChange(of:)` all use modern 2-arg form). 0 force-unwraps, 0 try!, 0 fatalError, 0 TODO/FIXME, 0 print leakage (all properly #if DEBUG-gated).\n   - User asked \"Are the tests modern syntax?\" — I scanned and found: 0 `@Test(arguments:)` parameterized tests, 0 tags, 0 withKnownIssue, 0 confirmation usage in Swift Testing suites; XCUITest files use 0 async tests and 0 `await fulfillment(of:)` (still using old `waitForExpectations`/`expectation(description:)`); several parameterizable candidate groups (APIServiceTests HTTP status 401/500, ReducerTests PageOne/PageTwo pairs across 6 reducers, PeopleActionsTests success/DoesNotDispatchOnFailure pairs, AppDataICloudBackupTests round-trips).\n\n6. All user messages:\n   - \"Ok lets start that\" (referring to starting Modernization 6 — initial pre-summary message but reconstructable from context)\n   - \"yes\" (proceeding with Modernization 6)\n   - \"Yes\" (merging PR #12 / starting it)\n   - \"Yes lets do a quick refresh to see if you find anything else\" (first audit refresh)\n   - (Selected via AskUserQuestion): \"cornerRadius sweep, Dead @available cleanup, Combine→async image loading\"\n   - \"Yes lets do a quick refresh to see if you find anything else\" (second audit refresh — said \"Yes lets do a quick refresh\" verbatim)\n   - \"Are the tests modern syntax?\" (most recent — asking about test code modernity beyond just framework migration)\n\n7. Pending Tasks:\n   - No explicit pending tasks from the user. The user asked \"Are the tests modern syntax?\" and I just completed the audit scan. The user has not yet responded to my scan results or selected what (if anything) to act on.\n\n8. Current Work:\n   I was responding to the user's question \"Are the tests modern syntax?\" by running an audit scan of test files for advanced Swift Testing features and modern XCTest patterns. The scan output revealed:\n   \n   - **Swift Testing advanced features unused**: 0 `@Test(arguments:)` parameterized tests, 0 `.tags`, 0 `withKnownIssue`, 0 `confirmation(` (I used custom withCheckedContinuation bridges instead).\n   - **XCUITest files using old patterns** (these must stay XCTest):\n     - MovieSwiftUITests.swift: 59 methods, 0 async, 10 old waitForExpectations/expectation(description:), 0 await fulfillment(of:)\n     - MovieSwiftMacUITests.swift: 38 methods, 0 async, 8 old wait, 0 await fulfillment\n     - MovieSwiftTVUITests.swift: 15 methods, 0 async, 0 old wait, 0 await fulfillment\n   - **Parameterizable candidate groups**:\n     - APIServiceTests: `getReturnsHTTPStatusFor401` + `getReturnsHTTPStatusFor500` (parameterizable on status code)\n     - ReducerTests: 12 tests in PageOne/PageTwo pairs across 6 reducers (SetMovieMenuList, SetSearch, SetMovieForGenre, SetMovieWithKeyword, peopleReducerSetSearch, peopleReducerSetPopular)\n     - PeopleActionsTests: 5 success/DoesNotDispatchOnFailure pairs (FetchDetail, FetchImages, FetchPeopleCredits, FetchMovieCasts, FetchSearch)\n     - AppDataICloudBackupTests: 11 @Test methods with round-trip shapes\n   \n   I had just run this comprehensive scan and received the output; I have not yet written up findings and recommendations for the user. The natural next step is to summarize findings and ask whether to act on any of the modernization opportunities (XCUITest async/await + `await fulfillment(of:)`, and/or `@Test(arguments:)` parameterization of similar test groups).\n\n9. Optional Next Step:\n   Present the test-modernity audit findings to the user with a clear recommendation. Specifically: (a) XCUITest files (MovieSwiftUITests + MovieSwiftMacUITests) still use `waitForExpectations` + `expectation(description:)` — these can be modernized to `func testX() async throws` + `await fulfillment(of:)`, which is current XCTest API. (b) Several Swift Testing suites have parameterizable test groups (most notably 12 PageOne/PageTwo reducer pairs and 5 PeopleActionsTests success/failure pairs) that could use `@Test(arguments:)`. The user just asked the question \"Are the tests modern syntax?\" so they want my assessment — I should report findings and ask which (if any) to act on, mirroring how I handled the prior audit refreshes via AskUserQuestion. Direct quote from the user's most recent message: \"Are the tests modern syntax?\"\n\nIf you need specific details from before compaction (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/scottdensmore/.claude/projects/-Users-scottdensmore-Developer-scottdensmore-movieswiftui/2cae28a4-28e8-4bfa-9225-7682543f3664.jsonl\nContinue the conversation from where it left off without asking the user any further questions. Resume directly — do not acknowledge the summary, do not recap what was happening, do not preface with \"I'll continue\" or similar. Pick up the last task as if the break never happened."},"isVisibleInTranscriptOnly":true,"isCompactSummary":true,"uuid":"48e806e4-6a4b-4d24-a07b-658d49833e08","timestamp":"2026-05-30T02:20:55.111Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-desktop","cwd":"/Users/scottdensmore/Developer/scottdensmore/movieswiftui","sessionId":"2cae28a4-28e8-4bfa-9225-7682543f3664","version":"2.1.149","gitBranch":"main","slug":"snuggly-shimmying-pebble"}
{"parentUuid":"48e806e4-6a4b-4d24-a07b-658d49833e08","isSidechain":false,"attachment":{"type":"file","filename":"/Users/scottdensmore/Developer/scottdensmore/movieswiftui/MovieSwift/Packages/Backend/Sources/Backend/services/ImageService.swift","content":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/scottdensmore/Developer/scottdensmore/movieswiftui/MovieSwift/Packages/Backend/Sources/Backend/services/ImageService.swift","content":"import Foundation\n\n// Stateless (no stored properties), so safe to share across threads —\n// the `shared` singleton requires `Sendable` under the Swift 6 mode.\npublic final class ImageService: Sendable {\n    public static let shared = ImageService()\n\n    public enum Size: String, Sendable {\n        case small = \"https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w154/\"\n        case medium = \"https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/\"\n        case cast = \"https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w185/\"\n        case original = \"https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/original/\"\n\n        public func path(poster: String) -> URL {\n            return URL(string: rawValue)!.appendingPathComponent(poster)\n        }\n    }\n\n    public enum ImageError: Error {\n        case decodingError\n    }\n\n    /// Fetches the raw image data, returning `nil` on any transport error\n    /// (matching the previous Combine pipeline's `.catch { Just(nil) }`).\n    public func fetchImage(poster: String, size: Size) async -> Data? {\n        do {\n            let (data, _) = try await URLSession.shared.data(from: size.path(poster: poster))\n            return data\n        } catch {\n            return nil\n        }\n    }\n}\n","numLines":34,"startLine":1,"totalLines":34}},"displayPath":"MovieSwift/Packages/Backend/Sources/Backend/services/ImageService.swift"},"type":"attachment","uuid":"b7448220-513b-42b1-a921-b8f68102a261","timestamp":"2026-05-30T02:20:54.915Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-desktop","cwd":"/Users/scottdensmore/Developer/scottdensmore/movieswiftui","sessionId":"2cae28a4-28e8-4bfa-9225-7682543f3664","version":"2.1.149","gitBranch":"main","slug":"snuggly-shimmying-pebble"}
{"parentUuid":"b7448220-513b-42b1-a921-b8f68102a261","isSidechain":false,"attachment":{"type":"file","filename":"/Users/scottdensmore/Developer/scottdensmore/movieswiftui/MovieSwift/Packages/Backend/Tests/BackendTests/ImageLoaderCacheTests.swift","content":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/scottdensmore/Developer/scottdensmore/movieswiftui/MovieSwift/Packages/Backend/Tests/BackendTests/ImageLoaderCacheTests.swift","content":"import Testing\n@testable import Backend\n\n// `@MainActor`: ImageLoaderCache / ImageLoader are main-actor-isolated.\n@Suite @MainActor\nstruct ImageLoaderCacheTests {\n    @Test func loaderForReturnsSameInstanceForSamePathAndSize() {\n        let cache = ImageLoaderCache()\n\n        let first = cache.loaderFor(path: \"/poster.jpg\", size: .small)\n        let second = cache.loaderFor(path: \"/poster.jpg\", size: .small)\n\n        #expect(first === second)\n    }\n\n    @Test func loaderForReturnsDifferentInstanceForDifferentSize() {\n        let cache = ImageLoaderCache()\n\n        let first = cache.loaderFor(path: \"/poster.jpg\", size: .small)\n        let second = cache.loaderFor(path: \"/poster.jpg\", size: .medium)\n\n        #expect(first !== second)\n    }\n\n    @Test func loaderForCachesMissingPathKey() {\n        let cache = ImageLoaderCache()\n\n        let first = cache.loaderFor(path: nil, size: .cast)\n        let second = cache.loaderFor(path: nil, size: .cast)\n\n        #expect(first === second)\n    }\n\n    @Test func clearRemovesCachedLoaders() {\n        let cache = ImageLoaderCache()\n\n        let first = cache.loaderFor(path: \"/poster.jpg\", size: .small)\n        cache.clear()\n        let second = cache.loaderFor(path: \"/poster.jpg\", size: .small)\n\n        #expect(first !== second)\n    }\n}\n","numLines":44,"startLine":1,"totalLines":44}},"displayPath":"MovieSwift/Packages/Backend/Tests/BackendTests/ImageLoaderCacheTests.swift"},"type":"attachment","uuid":"60f27772-2351-4881-b401-bdc95e690b2a","timestamp":"2026-05-30T02:20:54.915Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-desktop","cwd":"/Users/scottdensmore/Developer/scottdensmore/movieswiftui","sessionId":"2cae28a4-28e8-4bfa-9225-7682543f3664","version":"2.1.149","gitBranch":"main","slug":"snuggly-shimmying-pebble"}
