{"parentUuid":"beea7c0b-c00a-4746-927e-fc21f06eec86","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01L2M1FNavVvAr7AdncDHZ76","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01CGbRFsdDV6KD9EcE9wyaM9","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"git add MovieSwift/MovieSwiftUITests/MovieSwiftMacUITests.swift MovieSwift/MovieSwiftUITests/MovieSwiftUITests.swift && git commit -m \"$(cat <<'EOF'\ntest(ui): modernize XCUITest waits to async + await fulfillment(of:)\n\nReplaces the legacy waitForExpectations / sync wait(for:) pairs in the\niOS and macOS UI test cases with `async` test methods + `await\nfulfillment(of:[exp], timeout:)`. Each predicate-based\n`expectation(for:evaluatedWith:)` is now captured into a named `let`\nthat documents what we're actually waiting on (e.g. `dialogGone`,\n`formDismissed`, `toggleUpdated`, `pickerUpdated`), instead of relying\non the XCTestCase-implicit registration the old API used.\n\nThis is current XCTest API and removes the only `wait(for:)` /\n`waitForExpectations` sites in the project. XCUITest files must stay on\nXCTest (Swift Testing can't drive XCUIApplication) — this just brings\nthem up to modern XCTest patterns.\n\nTouches 10 iOS test methods (MovieSwiftUITests) and 8 macOS test\nmethods (MovieSwiftMacUITests). No behavior change.\nEOF\n)\"","description":"Commit XCUITest async/await modernization"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":218,"cache_read_input_tokens":99252,"output_tokens":552,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":218,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":552,"cache_read_input_tokens":99252,"cache_creation_input_tokens":218,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":218