{"parentUuid":"8ae2765b-9c90-4487-88a4-eb3181fba959","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01RsLiGT13jtvGoa7zXkttvV","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_016EwSnHMuHm2946gMmgNn1f","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"gh pr create --title \"test(ui): modernize XCUITest waits to async + await fulfillment(of:)\" --body \"$(cat <<'EOF'\n## Summary\n\n- Modernizes the XCUITest cases (`MovieSwiftUITests` + `MovieSwiftMacUITests`) from XCTestCase's legacy `waitForExpectations` / sync `wait(for:)` to `async` test methods + `await fulfillment(of:[exp], timeout:)`.\n- Each predicate-based `expectation(for:evaluatedWith:)` is now captured into a named `let` (e.g. `dialogGone`, `formDismissed`, `toggleUpdated`, `pickerUpdated`, `pickerUpdated`, `statusCleared`) that documents what each wait is actually for, rather than relying on the implicit XCTestCase registration the old API used.\n- Removes the only `wait(for:)` / `waitForExpectations` sites in the project.\n\n## Scope\n\nXCUITest files must stay on XCTest — Swift Testing can't drive `XCUIApplication`. This PR doesn't change that; it just brings the XCTest-side patterns up to current API (async test methods + `await fulfillment(of:)` were introduced in Xcode 13.3 / Swift 5.6).\n\n10 iOS test methods + 8 macOS test methods touched. No behavior change — same predicates, same timeouts, same assertions follow each wait.\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [ ] `xcodebuild build-for-testing -scheme MovieSwift -destination 'platform=iOS Simulator,name=iPhone 17 Pro' -only-testing:MovieSwiftUITests` succeeds locally (verified).\n- [ ] `xcodebuild build-for-testing -scheme MovieSwiftMac -destination 'platform=macOS' -only-testing:MovieSwiftMacUITests` succeeds locally (verified).\n- [ ] CI: `ios-tests`, `ios-tests-ipad`, `mac-tests`, `tvos-tests`, `package-tests`, Analyze (actions/ruby/swift), CodeQL all green.\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\nEOF\n)\"","description":"Open PR for XCUITest modernization"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":409,"cache_read_input_tokens":101578,"output_tokens":850,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":409,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":850,"cache_read_input_tokens":101578,"cache_creation_input_tokens":409,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":409},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CbXyF6Xtmi9sYuKWqZFaL","attributionMcpServer":"ccd_session","attributionMcpTool":"mark_chapter","type":"assistant","uuid":"3a9e2d37-4805-4780-9fd4-33887d1462f9","timestamp":"2026-05-30T02:33:09.733Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-desktop","cwd":"/Users/scottdensmore/Developer/scottdensmore/movieswiftui/MovieSwift","sessionId":"2cae28a4-28e8-4bfa-9225-7682543f3664","version":"2.1.149","gitBranch":"modernize/xcuitest-async-fulfillment","slug":"snuggly-shimmying-pebble"}
