{"parentUuid":"a9d0ca4a-1a7f-4288-9954-0e7f3c51ea5d","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01CjNCHmpUkNMDd6C1AJiZfk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_017Gg2wzYjnSNdcs3ifeR2Yv","name":"Agent","input":{"description":"Watch PR #15 and #16 CI","subagent_type":"general-purpose","run_in_background":true,"prompt":"Watch BOTH GitHub PRs #15 and #16 in repo scottdensmore/MovieSwiftUI until all required checks settle.\n\nPR #15 (branch modernize/xcuitest-async-fulfillment) is mostly done — only Analyze (swift) is still pending (~25 min total typical). All others passed last I checked.\n\nPR #16 (branch modernize/parameterize-reducer-tests) was just opened and all checks are pending.\n\nRequired checks for both: Analyze (actions), Analyze (ruby), Analyze (swift), CodeQL, ios-tests, ios-tests-ipad, mac-tests, package-tests, tvos-tests.\n\nSteps:\n1. For each PR: run `gh pr checks <num> --watch --interval 30 --repo scottdensmore/MovieSwiftUI` until it settles. Use the foreground `Bash` tool with a 600000ms timeout each. Watch #15 first (less remaining) then #16.\n2. After both settle, run `gh pr checks 15 --repo scottdensmore/MovieSwiftUI` and `gh pr checks 16 --repo scottdensmore/MovieSwiftUI` to capture final tables.\n3. For each PR: `gh pr view <N> --repo scottdensmore/MovieSwiftUI --json mergeable,mergeStateStatus -q '\"mergeable=\" + (.mergeable // \"null\") + \" state=\" + (.mergeStateStatus // \"null\")'`\n4. For each PR: check Copilot comments: `gh api \"repos/scottdensmore/MovieSwiftUI/pulls/<N>/comments\" --jq '[.[] | select(.user.login == \"copilot-pull-request-reviewer[bot]\") | {path: .path, line: .line, body: .body[0:300]}]'`\n\nReport (under 300 words):\n=== PR #15 settled ===\n<check<TAB>state<TAB>elapsed<TAB>url per line>\n=== PR #15 mergeable ===\nmergeable=<X> state=<Y>\n=== PR #15 Copilot ===\n<comments, or \"none\">\n=== PR #16 settled ===\n...\n=== PR #16 mergeable ===\n...\n=== PR #16 Copilot ===\n...\n\nDon't fork the watch into a separate background process — run it in the foreground in your own Bash call so you can capture its exit. If a watch hits 600s timeout before settling, just run `gh pr checks <N>` and report whatever state it has."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":966,"cache_read_input_tokens":159299,"output_tokens":1402,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":966,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":1402,"cache_read_input_tokens":159299,"cache_creation_input_tokens":966,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":966},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CbXzFundczAU9Fw74Y6Se","attributionMcpServer":"ccd_session","attributionMcpTool":"mark_chapter","type":"assistant","uuid":"ce9b37cb-256b-4019-8a42-00e15bf35e95","timestamp":"2026-05-30T02:46:36.421Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-desktop","cwd":"/Users/scottdensmore/Developer/scottdensmore/movieswiftui/MovieSwift/Packages/MovieSwiftFluxCore","sessionId":"2cae28a4-28e8-4bfa-9225-7682543f3664","version":"2.1.149","gitBranch":"modernize/parameterize-reducer-tests","slug":"snuggly-shimmying-pebble"}
