{"parentUuid":"5bd92422-abfb-453f-acc4-2b69423e22ce","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-7","id":"msg_01WXoMnHdeyPeZP4zzJ6XSwd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_0137QmSiijbwWLaUfctfmifP","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"gh pr create --base main --head modernize/parameterize-people-actions-tests --title \"test(people-actions): parameterize 5 DoesNotDispatchOnFailure tests with @Test(arguments:)\" --body \"$(cat <<'EOF'\n## Summary\n\n- Collapses 5 nearly-identical `fetchXDoesNotDispatchOnFailure` tests in `PeopleActionsTests` into one parameterized test `fetchActionDoesNotDispatchDataActionOnFailure(kind:)` that iterates over a `FailureFetchKind` enum (`.fetchDetail`, `.fetchImages`, `.fetchPeopleCredits`, `.fetchMovieCasts`, `.fetchSearch`).\n- The dispatch indirection goes through an instance-method switch rather than a struct of `@Sendable` closures, so `DispatchFunction` (a non-Sendable function type) doesn't have to cross the `@Test(arguments:)` boundary.\n\n## What stays as-is — and why\n\n- **Success-side tests** (`fetchXDispatchesSetXOnSuccess`) stay individual. Each one verifies action-specific invariants (FetchDetail asserts `person.id`/`name`, FetchMovieCasts also asserts URL path `/movie/99/credits`, FetchSearch asserts `query`/`page`/`results.first?.name`, etc.). Forcing them into a single signature with case-by-case assertions would obscure intent without removing meaningful duplication.\n- **FetchPopular's pair** stays split. Its failure path dispatches `PopularRequestFailed` rather than just \"not dispatching `SetPopular`\", so it doesn't fit the shared `DoesNotDispatchOnFailure` shape the other 5 share.\n\n## Access detail\n\nThe `@Test` method is marked `private` because its parameter type `FailureFetchKind` is private. Swift Testing's macros do work on private methods, so this is fine.\n\n## Test count\n\nPeopleActionsTests goes from 12 tests to 8 tests (5 success + 1 parameterized failure covering 5 cases + 2 FetchPopular). All green locally — `xcodebuild test ... -only-testing:MovieSwiftTests/PeopleActionsTests` passes.\n\n## Test plan\n\n- [ ] xcodebuild test -only-testing:MovieSwiftTests/PeopleActionsTests succeeds locally (verified — 8 tests, 1 suite, green).\n- [ ] CI: ios-tests, ios-tests-ipad, mac-tests, tvos-tests, package-tests, Analyze (actions/ruby/swift), CodeQL all green.\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\nEOF\n)\"","description":"Open PR for PeopleActionsTests parameterization"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":419,"cache_read_input_tokens":199947,"output_tokens":1032,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":419,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[{"input_tokens":1,"output_tokens":1032,"cache_read_input_tokens":199947,"cache_creation_input_tokens":419,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":419},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CbXzox4wiQoPmhE25rkLs","attributionMcpServer":"ccd_session","attributionMcpTool":"mark_chapter","type":"assistant","uuid":"67b37289-059d-423f-9428-74d6a5447227","timestamp":"2026-05-30T02:53:43.641Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-desktop","cwd":"/Users/scottdensmore/Developer/scottdensmore/movieswiftui/MovieSwift","sessionId":"2cae28a4-28e8-4bfa-9225-7682543f3664","version":"2.1.149","gitBranch":"modernize/parameterize-people-actions-tests","slug":"snuggly-shimmying-pebble"}
